428
00:40:54,518 --> 00:40:56,577
Get off him!

429
00:40:57,588 --> 00:40:59,613
How did this happen?

430
00:41:00,257 --> 00:41:02,054
Who is to blame?

431
00:41:04,261 --> 00:41:05,819
SOLA: Woola.

432
00:41:27,852 --> 00:41:30,082
Do that again and I... (GRUNTS)

433
00:41:34,225 --> 00:41:36,523
(DRUMMING RESUMES
AND STOPS AT INTERVALS)

434
00:41:45,236 --> 00:41:46,203
(CRIES OUT)

435
00:41:52,409 --> 00:41:53,706
Enough!

436
00:42:01,585 --> 00:42:05,783
There is no room
for another mark, Sola.

437
00:42:08,425 --> 00:42:10,689
Your next offense will be your last.

438
00:42:24,875 --> 00:42:26,900
You will jump, Virginia.

439
00:42:27,578 --> 00:42:28,875
Now.

440
00:42:29,013 --> 00:42:30,844
Jeddak! Fliers!

441
00:42:30,948 --> 00:42:32,813
You are the stones, the sand!

442
00:42:33,417 --> 00:42:35,317
(SHOUTING)

443
00:42:51,135 --> 00:42:53,433
Sir, they continue to ignore our signals.

444
00:42:54,071 --> 00:42:57,006
Enough! I've been patient.
I'll not be mocked.

445
00:42:57,107 --> 00:42:58,506
Let them die!

446
00:43:01,278 --> 00:43:04,247
If that's how you plan
to treat your future bride,

447
00:43:04,381 --> 00:43:06,372
it's no wonder she ran from you.

448
00:43:07,117 --> 00:43:09,415
Dejah Thoris must live.

449
00:43:09,553 --> 00:43:10,747
In range, sir.

450
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:12,688
MATAl: You need only cripple the ship.

451
00:43:12,790 --> 00:43:15,384
A pulse to the radium drive
will be sufficient.

452
00:43:15,726 --> 00:43:18,490
Quick, clean, and precise.

453
00:43:18,929 --> 00:43:20,954
Jeddak, shall we destroy her?

454
00:43:21,498 --> 00:43:22,590
No.

455
00:43:22,733 --> 00:43:24,257
We need only cripple her.

456
00:43:24,368 --> 00:43:25,801
Now bring us around.

457
00:43:25,903 --> 00:43:26,961
Zodanga.

458
00:43:27,104 --> 00:43:29,129
- Helium.
- Helium.

459
00:43:29,273 --> 00:43:30,467
Helium.

460
00:43:30,608 --> 00:43:31,939
Zodanga.

461
00:43:32,076 --> 00:43:34,306
They are the red flag, Helium the blue.

462
00:43:34,445 --> 00:43:36,572
Zodanga's winning the war,

463
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:40,946
but I say let red men kill red men
until only Tharks remain.

464
00:43:49,426 --> 00:43:50,916
(CHEERING)

465
00:43:52,529 --> 00:43:53,826
That don't look like a fair fight.

466
00:43:53,964 --> 00:43:56,228
Zodanga never fights fair.

467
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:04,464
Where is she?

468
00:44:04,608 --> 00:44:05,597
My Jeddak, that's all of them.

469
00:44:05,709 --> 00:44:07,472
She can't have just
vanished into thin air.

470
00:44:07,578 --> 00:44:09,375
- Check the dead.
- We have, sire.

471
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:11,175
Then check them again.

472
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:19,619
(MEN YELLING)

473
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:21,190
To the bridge, now!

474
00:44:21,625 --> 00:44:23,149
(SCREAMING)

475
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:29,127
(SCREAMING) Look out!

476
00:44:30,868 --> 00:44:31,857
(CHEERING)

477
00:44:38,676 --> 00:44:41,144
(SCREAMING)

478
00:44:43,147 --> 00:44:44,444
She's a human!

479
00:44:45,382 --> 00:44:46,349
(ALL GASP)

480
00:44:46,483 --> 00:44:48,417
Sola!

481
00:44:56,260 --> 00:44:57,284
Who is that?

482
00:44:58,028 --> 00:44:59,791
I betVirginia.

483
00:45:03,834 --> 00:45:04,892
Beg your pardon, ma'am.

484
00:45:05,335 --> 00:45:07,360
If you'll kindly just stand behind me.

485
00:45:07,504 --> 00:45:09,267
This might get dangerous.

486
00:45:28,726 --> 00:45:31,286
Or maybe I ought to get behind you.

487
00:45:35,733 --> 00:45:37,758
You let me know
when it gets dangerous.

488
00:46:24,515 --> 00:46:25,880
No.

489
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:27,978
Take him alive.

490
00:46:28,085 --> 00:46:31,145
What's the point of having this thing
if I don't get to use it?

491
00:46:34,958 --> 00:46:35,982
Leave him!

492
00:46:40,197 --> 00:46:41,391
(GRUNTING)

493
00:46:57,648 --> 00:46:59,081
What are you?

494
00:46:59,183 --> 00:47:01,913
You aren't red man nor quite white ape!

495
00:47:03,887 --> 00:47:05,479
No matter.

496
00:47:05,622 --> 00:47:07,191
You can still bleed like...

497
00:47:08,725 --> 00:47:09,817
Tharks!

498
00:47:10,127 --> 00:47:11,594
Fire!

499
00:47:21,004 --> 00:47:22,335
DEJAH: I surrender.

500
00:47:22,472 --> 00:47:24,497
You may take me captive.

501
00:47:33,817 --> 00:47:35,614
Prepare to turn about!

502
00:47:41,325 --> 00:47:43,350
(CHEERING)

503
00:47:43,727 --> 00:47:45,319
(CHEERING CONTINUES)

504
00:47:45,462 --> 00:47:47,157
Did I not tell you he could jump?

505
00:47:47,264 --> 00:47:49,357
Oh, my God.

506
00:47:51,201 --> 00:47:53,066
Let go! Bad dog!

507
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,967
You are ugly, but you are beautiful.

508
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:58,933
And you fight like a Thark.

509
00:48:02,079 --> 00:48:04,707
You lost your wager. You must pay.

510
00:48:06,049 --> 00:48:08,074
Jeddak of the Tharks.

511
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:12,647
I am Dejah Thoris,

512
00:48:12,756 --> 00:48:15,350
regent of the Royal Helium
Academy of Science.

513
00:48:15,459 --> 00:48:18,519
- My research vessel...
- Your share of the spoils.

514
00:48:18,629 --> 00:48:20,722
Sola! Tend to Virginia's property.

515
00:48:20,831 --> 00:48:21,889
Yes, my Jeddak!

516
00:48:22,032 --> 00:48:23,897
You know once Sab Than
has conquered us,

517
00:48:24,034 --> 00:48:26,025
he will turn his weapon upon you!

518
00:48:26,136 --> 00:48:29,697
I know that Zodanga
has found a way to defeat you

519
00:48:29,806 --> 00:48:33,242
and now you seek
a mighty weapon of your own.

520
00:48:33,777 --> 00:48:36,644
But Virginia fights for us!

521
00:48:38,115 --> 00:48:41,482
- He'll fight the Torquas in the south...
- (CHEERING)

522
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:43,917
...the Warhoon in the north

523
00:48:44,054 --> 00:48:47,854
and he will be called Dotar Sojat,

524
00:48:47,958 --> 00:48:50,051
- my right arms!
- (CHEERING)

525
00:48:51,628 --> 00:48:53,459
No.

526
00:48:56,233 --> 00:48:58,258
I don't fight for anyone.

527
00:49:05,976 --> 00:49:09,104
Virginia, reject this honor

528
00:49:09,246 --> 00:49:13,046
and I cannot guarantee
the safety of your red girl.

529
00:49:24,161 --> 00:49:27,653
I am

530
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:32,059
Dotar Sojat!

531
00:49:32,502 --> 00:49:34,595
(CHEERING)

532
00:49:34,705 --> 00:49:36,764
To the plunder!

533
00:50:05,402 --> 00:50:07,495
War is a shameful thing.

534
00:50:11,675 --> 00:50:15,270
Not when a noble cause is taken up
by those who can make a difference.

535
00:50:20,050 --> 00:50:22,109
You made a difference today, Virginia.

536
00:50:24,187 --> 00:50:25,552
Okay.

537
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:28,317
See, my name is John Carter.

538
00:50:29,092 --> 00:50:31,390
Virginia is where I'm from.

539
00:50:31,862 --> 00:50:34,023
Where did you learn to jump that way?

540
00:50:34,164 --> 00:50:35,961
I don't know.

541
00:50:36,066 --> 00:50:37,897
How'd you learn to fly?

542
00:50:38,568 --> 00:50:42,629
Your ships cannot sail
on light in Virginia?

543
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,507
No, Professor.

544
00:50:44,841 --> 00:50:47,036
See, our ships sail the seas.

545
00:50:50,247 --> 00:50:52,147
Endless water everywhere.

546
00:50:59,089 --> 00:51:00,386
Skeletal structure normal.

547
00:51:00,524 --> 00:51:02,014
What are you doing?

548
00:51:02,125 --> 00:51:04,184
Must be the density of your bones.

549
00:51:05,028 --> 00:51:07,394
- Jump for me.
- SOLA: Enough!

550
00:51:07,531 --> 00:51:09,499
There will be time for playfulness later.

551
00:51:09,599 --> 00:51:11,863
I want no playfulness from him.

552
00:51:11,968 --> 00:51:13,196
I want his help.

553
00:51:14,037 --> 00:51:15,766
Explain to me how you do it.

554
00:51:17,307 --> 00:51:19,867
If it's a skill, teach it to Helium.

555
00:51:20,777 --> 00:51:24,076
- Name your price.
- I'm not for hire.

556
00:51:26,783 --> 00:51:29,343
I've got a cave of gold of my own.

557
00:51:29,453 --> 00:51:31,114
Somewhere.

558
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:34,686
Only a madman would rave
about the time of oceans.

559
00:51:34,791 --> 00:51:36,782
Is that your expert view?

560
00:51:36,927 --> 00:51:39,691
- I'm mad?
- Or a liar.

561
00:51:39,796 --> 00:51:41,855
She is a good match for you,
Dotar Sojat.

562
00:51:41,965 --> 00:51:43,432
Don't call me that.

563
00:51:43,567 --> 00:51:45,831
There are no seas on the planet.

564
00:51:48,905 --> 00:51:50,634
You said "planet."

565
00:51:53,810 --> 00:51:56,040
DEJAH: Sun, then Rasoom.

566
00:51:56,146 --> 00:51:57,238
JOHN: Mercury.

567
00:51:57,347 --> 00:51:59,406
Then Cosoom.

568
00:51:59,916 --> 00:52:02,077
Venus.

569
00:52:02,185 --> 00:52:04,085
Then Earth... us.

570
00:52:05,589 --> 00:52:07,614
That is Jasoom.

571
00:52:08,291 --> 00:52:11,192
You are on Barsoom, John Carter.

572
00:52:12,295 --> 00:52:14,320
Mars.

573
00:52:14,865 --> 00:52:16,230
I'm on Mars?

574
00:52:28,945 --> 00:52:30,810
Good God.

575
00:52:30,947 --> 00:52:32,972
I'm on Mars.

576
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:39,243
So, now home is Jasoom

577
00:52:39,356 --> 00:52:41,449
and you came on one
of your sailing ships

578
00:52:41,558 --> 00:52:43,583
across millions
of karads of empty space?

579
00:52:43,693 --> 00:52:46,423
No. Not like that.

580
00:52:47,063 --> 00:52:49,725
Go on, shock me.

581
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,024
How?

582
00:52:53,537 --> 00:52:55,596
That brought me here.

583
00:53:04,714 --> 00:53:05,840
Oh.

584
00:53:06,750 --> 00:53:09,218
Well, that explains everything, then.

585
00:53:10,153 --> 00:53:13,122
- It does?
- Yes.

586
00:53:13,223 --> 00:53:14,383
You're a Thern

587
00:53:15,091 --> 00:53:17,150
and you simply
wish to return to your rightful place.

588
00:53:17,260 --> 00:53:18,227
Isn't that it?

589
00:53:18,495 --> 00:53:19,621
Yes.

590
00:53:19,729 --> 00:53:21,629
Then let's sort this out right now.

591
00:53:21,731 --> 00:53:23,790
Come along!

592
00:53:29,272 --> 00:53:30,705
(GROWLS)

593
00:53:31,942 --> 00:53:33,500
SOLA: Where are you going?

594
00:53:33,610 --> 00:53:35,475
DEJAH: To your temple.

595
00:53:36,746 --> 00:53:38,805
No. No, you cannot enter here.

596
00:53:40,917 --> 00:53:42,578
It is forbidden!

597
00:53:43,286 --> 00:53:44,583
You are not Thark!

598
00:53:44,688 --> 00:53:45,848
(BARK)

599
00:53:46,356 --> 00:53:47,880
Woola, stay!

600
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:08,710
(WHISPERS) Dotar Sojat.

601
00:54:08,812 --> 00:54:09,938
It is forbidden.

602
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:11,342
It is forbidden!

603
00:54:12,649 --> 00:54:15,243
Well, you speak for the Goddess.

604
00:54:17,420 --> 00:54:18,682
What does she say?

605
00:54:21,791 --> 00:54:23,782
You called me a Thern.

606
00:54:24,227 --> 00:54:25,592
Is that what she is?

607
00:54:25,729 --> 00:54:28,220
No, she is Issus.

608
00:54:28,331 --> 00:54:31,095
Therns are holy messengers
of the Goddess.

609
00:54:31,234 --> 00:54:33,998
In the time of oceans,
they walked among us, guiding us.

610
00:54:34,838 --> 00:54:35,964
We must not offend.

611
00:54:36,139 --> 00:54:37,902
Let us go.

612
00:54:40,076 --> 00:54:42,340
There's some kind of writing up there.

613
00:54:43,813 --> 00:54:45,872
(DEJAH SHRIEKS)

614
00:54:46,349 --> 00:54:47,873
(JOHN GROANS)

615
00:54:48,318 --> 00:54:49,376
(PRAYS)

616
00:54:58,094 --> 00:55:00,528
- Can you read it?
- It's old scripture.

617
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:02,598
There it is again.

618
00:55:02,699 --> 00:55:05,259
- What's it mean?
- Don't rush me.

619
00:55:05,368 --> 00:55:07,928
"Those who seek the solace of eternity

620
00:55:08,438 --> 00:55:10,838
"may journey down the river

621
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:12,771
"through the sacred Gates of Iss

622
00:55:12,876 --> 00:55:15,344
"and find everlasting peace

623
00:55:15,478 --> 00:55:16,911
"in the bosom of Issus."

624
00:55:19,482 --> 00:55:21,541
JOHN: The Gates of Iss.

625
00:55:26,456 --> 00:55:28,481
What if I could take you there?

626
00:55:34,397 --> 00:55:36,456
What if I didn't trust you?

627
00:55:38,368 --> 00:55:40,427
Then we'd be even.

628
00:55:42,138 --> 00:55:45,938
I can take you to the Gates,
to the answers that you seek.

629
00:55:47,577 --> 00:55:49,169
A way back to Jasoom.

630
00:55:49,312 --> 00:55:51,143
- Earth.
- Earth.

631
00:55:51,247 --> 00:55:54,114
It's the least I could do
to repay you for getting us out of here.

632
00:55:56,086 --> 00:55:57,747
Assuming that you can.

633
00:56:04,594 --> 00:56:06,653
Deal.

634
00:56:08,898 --> 00:56:11,025
Go on.

635
00:56:11,167 --> 00:56:12,657
You shake it.

636
00:56:12,769 --> 00:56:14,031
As a sign of trust.

637
00:56:17,207 --> 00:56:18,936
Good enough.

638
00:56:24,547 --> 00:56:28,381
Now all I need to do
is get this medallion off Tars Tarkas.

639
00:56:29,686 --> 00:56:31,711
SOLA: Dotar Sojat?

640
00:56:31,955 --> 00:56:32,979
(WEAPON IS COCKED)

641
00:56:33,089 --> 00:56:35,353
Useless she-calot.

642
00:56:36,926 --> 00:56:38,325
(WEAPONS ARE COCKED)

643
00:56:38,428 --> 00:56:39,588
I told you.

644
00:56:39,729 --> 00:56:41,629
It is forbidden.

645
00:56:42,165 --> 00:56:44,133
(GROANING)

646
00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:48,128
(GRUNTS)

647
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:50,399
What in the name of Issus is going on?

648
00:56:50,573 --> 00:56:52,040
Issus has been profaned.

649
00:56:52,175 --> 00:56:54,973
We found this one and the red wench
plotting in the temple.

650
00:56:55,111 --> 00:56:57,045
In the temple? How did they get...

651
00:56:57,180 --> 00:56:59,011
Sola led them there.

652
00:56:59,115 --> 00:57:01,049
Sola tried to stop us.

653
00:57:01,251 --> 00:57:03,344
I meant no disrespect
to your goddess, Tars.

654
00:57:03,453 --> 00:57:04,750
I'm just trying to get home.

655
00:57:04,888 --> 00:57:07,413
Your right arms were planning
to rob you of the medallion

656
00:57:07,557 --> 00:57:11,084
and use it to commit greater blasphemy
down the River Iss.

657
00:57:11,227 --> 00:57:13,195
They must all die in the arena.

658
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:17,666
How could you do this?
I spared your life.

659
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:22,003
I made you Dotar Sojat
yet her life means nothing to you.

660
00:57:22,272 --> 00:57:26,003
You knew... You knew
she had no room for another mark.

661
00:57:26,209 --> 00:57:29,269
Now Sola will die because of you.

662
00:57:31,214 --> 00:57:33,842
She's your daughter, isn't she?

663
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:39,422
(GRUNTS)

664
00:57:41,925 --> 00:57:43,358
Who told you that?

665
00:57:43,493 --> 00:57:45,324
Call it a father's intuition.

666
00:57:45,495 --> 00:57:47,190
A Thark has no parent but the horde.

667
00:57:47,330 --> 00:57:48,922
But how do you know?

668
00:57:51,067 --> 00:57:53,262
Her mother kept her egg

669
00:57:53,503 --> 00:57:55,937
and Sola's the last flicker
of her ancient greatness.

670
00:57:56,072 --> 00:57:58,063
You can't just stand here
and let her be killed.

671
00:57:59,175 --> 00:58:00,267
Argh!

672
00:58:01,177 --> 00:58:02,872
My right arms offend me.

673
00:58:02,979 --> 00:58:04,708
I will cut them off.

674
00:58:08,084 --> 00:58:09,608
No.

675
00:58:12,589 --> 00:58:14,819
You must hurry. I mean to release you.

676
00:58:16,192 --> 00:58:18,160
I make one condition.

677
00:58:18,728 --> 00:58:21,629
You take Sola with you
down the River Iss.

678
00:58:21,798 --> 00:58:22,958
My Jeddak.

679
00:58:24,133 --> 00:58:26,067
I'd rather you died
in the arms of the Goddess

680
00:58:26,169 --> 00:58:29,070
than as food
for wild banths in the arena.

681
00:58:30,039 --> 00:58:31,973
Where you go, she goes.

682
00:58:32,141 --> 00:58:33,608
What's gonna happen to you, Tars?

683
00:58:33,710 --> 00:58:37,202
Leave a Thark his head and one hand
and he may yet conquer.

684
00:58:42,652 --> 00:58:44,119
Is it done, my Jeddak?

685
00:58:48,391 --> 00:58:50,359
Tars Tarkas betrays us.

686
00:58:53,963 --> 00:58:55,191
JOHN: Woola!

687
00:58:55,398 --> 00:58:56,763
You belong to him.

688
00:58:56,900 --> 00:58:59,368
Woola would follow you
anywhere on Barsoom.

689
00:58:59,903 --> 00:59:02,463
DEJAH: It's three days' ride. Follow me.

690
00:59:17,253 --> 00:59:19,187
JOHN: What happened to this place?

691
00:59:19,422 --> 00:59:21,390
DEJAH: Zodanga happened.

692
01:00:09,472 --> 01:00:11,440
Sailing on light.

693
01:00:13,876 --> 01:00:15,844
Still playing the madman?

694
01:00:17,880 --> 01:00:19,370
Or the liar.

695
01:00:33,162 --> 01:00:35,687
DEJAH: Keep moving! We'll get there!

696
01:00:42,705 --> 01:00:45,640
SAB THAN: Why pursue this wedding
any longer? I've already won.

697
01:00:45,742 --> 01:00:48,734
Not yet. You must aim past the horizon,
Sab Than.

698
01:00:48,845 --> 01:00:52,838
To truly demoralize a nation requires a
public spectacle on the grandest scale.

699
01:00:52,949 --> 01:00:56,009
Staging this wedding will ensure
your rule goes unchallenged.

700
01:00:56,119 --> 01:00:57,711
If you insist.

701
01:00:58,187 --> 01:01:02,089
If you cannot see the wisdom in that,
then we will find another who can.

702
01:01:16,839 --> 01:01:18,807
Dotar Sojat.

703
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:22,102
Carter!

704
01:01:22,578 --> 01:01:24,512
I do not think she leads us to the Iss.

705
01:01:31,054 --> 01:01:32,988
All right, then, Sola.

706
01:01:33,189 --> 01:01:35,157
Just play along.

707
01:01:36,759 --> 01:01:37,748
(GASPS)

708
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:40,795
What do you think I'd do
once I saw your city and not some river?

709
01:01:40,963 --> 01:01:42,624
- What do you mean?
- Cluros and Thuria.

710
01:01:43,566 --> 01:01:45,056
They should be at our backs by now.

711
01:01:45,168 --> 01:01:47,466
You lead us toward Helium!

712
01:01:51,407 --> 01:01:53,671
Once we reach there,

713
01:01:53,776 --> 01:01:56,142
you would see for yourself
the virtue of our cause.

714
01:01:56,245 --> 01:01:57,439
(SCOFFS)

715
01:01:57,547 --> 01:02:01,415
Everyone thinks
their cause is virtuous... Professor.

716
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:03,610
DEJAH: What are you doing?

717
01:02:04,320 --> 01:02:05,344
(GRUNTS)

718
01:02:08,191 --> 01:02:09,317
No!

719
01:02:09,892 --> 01:02:11,382
John Carter!

720
01:02:11,594 --> 01:02:13,186
You can't!

721
01:02:13,329 --> 01:02:14,921
I like this plan better.

722
01:02:15,064 --> 01:02:16,554
Just wait.

723
01:02:16,699 --> 01:02:18,098
She'll come around.

724
01:02:18,201 --> 01:02:20,135
You mad fool!

725
01:02:20,636 --> 01:02:23,833
You're not from Earth!
There are no Therns!

726
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:26,800
I only told you what you wanted to hear
so you'd get us out!

727
01:02:27,643 --> 01:02:28,667
Stop!

728
01:02:28,778 --> 01:02:30,075
I can't!

729
01:02:30,213 --> 01:02:32,181
I cannot marry him!

730
01:02:36,219 --> 01:02:37,481
Can't marry who?

731
01:02:40,048 --> 01:02:42,107
The Zodangan Jeddak you fought.

732
01:02:42,217 --> 01:02:44,185
Sab Than.

733
01:02:44,786 --> 01:02:48,017
He offered a truce to my father
in exchange for my hand.

734
01:02:48,223 --> 01:02:49,713
Your father?

735
01:02:50,358 --> 01:02:52,189
Tardos Mors.

736
01:02:52,360 --> 01:02:55,454
The Jeddak of Helium.
She is a princess!

737
01:02:57,065 --> 01:02:58,760
A princess of Mars.

738
01:02:59,367 --> 01:03:01,335
How about that?

739
01:03:02,137 --> 01:03:06,198
A princess who didn't want
to get married, so she ran away.

740
01:03:06,741 --> 01:03:08,140
No.

741
01:03:08,276 --> 01:03:10,437
Is that all there is to the story?

742
01:03:11,012 --> 01:03:13,776
No, I didn't run away!

743
01:03:13,949 --> 01:03:17,009
- I escaped!
- From what, his breath?

744
01:03:17,319 --> 01:03:19,446
So marry the guy and save your people.

745
01:03:19,588 --> 01:03:22,318
A life of oppression!
That's not living! (GASPS)

746
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:34,234
If you had the means to save others,

747
01:03:34,336 --> 01:03:37,362
would you not take
any action possible to make it so?

748
01:03:38,340 --> 01:03:40,774
No good will come
out of me fighting your war.

749
01:03:43,244 --> 01:03:45,712
I would lay down my life for Helium.

750
01:03:50,585 --> 01:03:52,678
Yes, I ran away.

751
01:03:53,788 --> 01:03:55,756
I was afraid,

752
01:03:56,658 --> 01:03:57,989
weak.

753
01:04:00,862 --> 01:04:02,830
Maybe I should have married.

754
01:04:07,068 --> 01:04:10,697
But I so feared that it would somehow
be the end of Barsoom.

755
01:04:14,743 --> 01:04:18,008
I tell you truly, John Carter of Earth,

756
01:04:19,748 --> 01:04:21,613
there are no Gates of Iss.

757
01:04:22,651 --> 01:04:23,879
They are not real.

758
01:04:31,359 --> 01:04:33,327
I'm sorry, Princess.

759
01:04:36,698 --> 01:04:39,132
But this, this is real.

760
01:04:43,271 --> 01:04:45,239
And so is my cave of gold.

761
01:04:57,419 --> 01:04:59,444
Prudence demands you take an escort.

762
01:04:59,554 --> 01:05:00,851
No.

763
01:05:00,955 --> 01:05:02,923
I go alone, General.

764
01:05:04,759 --> 01:05:05,817
But, Jeddak...

765
01:05:05,927 --> 01:05:08,953
In one sweep, I can
put an end to 1,000 years of civil war

766
01:05:09,064 --> 01:05:11,157
and bring Helium to its knees forever.

767
01:05:12,033 --> 01:05:15,969
But my general, in his superior wisdom,
objects. Is that right?

768
01:05:20,675 --> 01:05:22,700
I'm starting to talk like you.

769
01:05:33,388 --> 01:05:35,379
THERN 1:
Hekkador, they have reached the Iss.

770
01:05:35,523 --> 01:05:36,990
It took them longer than I thought.

771
01:05:37,092 --> 01:05:38,081
THERN 2: If they reach the Gates...

772
01:05:38,226 --> 01:05:39,386
THERN 3:
They can breach the sanctuary.

773
01:05:39,527 --> 01:05:41,392
THERN 4: Her knowledge
of the Ninth Ray is already...

774
01:05:41,529 --> 01:05:43,326
MATAl: As advanced as it will ever be.

775
01:05:43,431 --> 01:05:44,796
Patience, brothers.

776
01:05:44,966 --> 01:05:46,934
It is under my control.

777
01:05:47,902 --> 01:05:49,870
I'm already there.

778
01:06:03,918 --> 01:06:05,886
SOLA: The Iss.

779
01:06:06,454 --> 01:06:09,287
Here, pilgrims must leave
behind all they have,

780
01:06:10,992 --> 01:06:13,051
all they know,

781
01:06:13,428 --> 01:06:15,020
never to return.

782
01:06:18,099 --> 01:06:20,499
May the Goddess find me worthy.

783
01:06:28,276 --> 01:06:29,607
Wait!

784
01:06:32,313 --> 01:06:33,439
What do you think you're doing?

785
01:06:33,782 --> 01:06:36,842
It is my way, Dotar Sojat, not yours.

786
01:06:36,951 --> 01:06:40,079
I must honor my Jeddak
and redeem my unworthiness!

787
01:06:40,413 --> 01:06:43,678
You want to honor your father?
Then stay alive and help me.

788
01:06:43,816 --> 01:06:45,340
(GASPS)

789
01:06:47,387 --> 01:06:49,116
My father?

790
01:06:51,224 --> 01:06:53,089
Sola...

791
01:06:53,259 --> 01:06:55,193
Why would you say that?

792
01:06:55,328 --> 01:06:57,353
That's what drives your compassion,

793
01:06:57,964 --> 01:07:01,024
the blood of your father, Tars Tarkas.

794
01:07:02,068 --> 01:07:06,061
And of all the Tharks,
you're the only one worthy of him.

795
01:07:16,949 --> 01:07:20,146
Your duty to your father
demands that you see me through.

796
01:07:22,221 --> 01:07:24,189
Just help me find the Gates.

797
01:07:24,724 --> 01:07:27,215
Then you can decide
what honor requires.

798
01:07:31,697 --> 01:07:33,562
Just to the Gates, then.

799
01:07:35,768 --> 01:07:37,929
Woola, stay!

800
01:07:38,805 --> 01:07:40,773
(WOOLA WHINES)

801
01:08:06,499 --> 01:08:08,467
(LOW VOICES)

802
01:08:14,340 --> 01:08:16,308
Other pilgrims.

803
01:08:29,689 --> 01:08:31,088
Professor.

804
01:08:31,290 --> 01:08:33,258
(RECITES PRAYER)

805
01:08:35,661 --> 01:08:37,060
Impossible.

806
01:08:43,803 --> 01:08:46,431
I've never seen
this kind of structure before.

807
01:08:49,442 --> 01:08:51,034
JOHN: I want to get a better look.

808
01:08:52,211 --> 01:08:53,473
(GASPS)

809
01:09:05,825 --> 01:09:08,191
Carter, your feet.

810
01:09:13,232 --> 01:09:15,200
(RUMBLING AND CRACKING)

811
01:09:43,696 --> 01:09:45,664
(LOW GROWL)

812
01:10:00,112 --> 01:10:02,080
This is not the work of gods.

813
01:10:04,116 --> 01:10:06,084
These are machines.

814
01:10:18,931 --> 01:10:20,193
Your medallion.

815
01:10:41,954 --> 01:10:43,922
A spider.

816
01:10:52,164 --> 01:10:53,324
Nine.

817
01:10:54,467 --> 01:10:55,934
Nine rays.

818
01:10:56,769 --> 01:10:57,963
Nine.

819
01:10:58,104 --> 01:10:59,571
The Ninth Ray is real.

820
01:10:59,672 --> 01:11:01,037
It can be harnessed. Do you see?

821
01:11:01,140 --> 01:11:03,973
This entire structure runs
on Ninth Ray isolates.

822
01:11:04,810 --> 01:11:06,744
Mother Issus!

823
01:11:06,979 --> 01:11:08,947
Such power.

824
01:11:10,549 --> 01:11:12,517
And somehow Zodanga has it.

825
01:11:16,789 --> 01:11:18,757
The Therns.

826
01:11:20,192 --> 01:11:22,160
They must be real.

827
01:11:22,962 --> 01:11:24,054
And you

828
01:11:27,466 --> 01:11:29,627
are John Carter of Earth?

829
01:11:31,370 --> 01:11:32,860
Yes, ma'am.

830
01:11:37,310 --> 01:11:39,278
And the ships

831
01:11:40,346 --> 01:11:42,314
that sail on the sea.

832
01:11:44,417 --> 01:11:46,385
You've seen them.

833
01:11:48,621 --> 01:11:50,589
That must be a beautiful sight.

834
01:11:51,657 --> 01:11:52,817
It truly is.

835
01:11:56,495 --> 01:11:57,792
(GASPS)

836
01:12:01,534 --> 01:12:03,832
It's our solar system.

837
01:12:17,249 --> 01:12:18,978
- What's it say?
- I'm not sure.

838
01:12:19,085 --> 01:12:20,643
What do you think it says?

839
01:12:20,753 --> 01:12:24,154
It appears to be
a kind of technical diagram.

840
01:12:24,990 --> 01:12:27,424
Here is Barsoom. There is Jasoom.

841
01:12:28,361 --> 01:12:29,555
This glyph here,

842
01:12:29,662 --> 01:12:33,530
it's like our symbol
for a transcription, a copy,

843
01:12:33,999 --> 01:12:37,093
sent along these lines here,
between the worlds.

844
01:12:37,336 --> 01:12:38,325
Like...

845
01:12:38,437 --> 01:12:40,405
A telegram.

846
01:12:41,240 --> 01:12:43,333
You're saying I was telegraphed here.

847
01:12:44,677 --> 01:12:46,577
I'm a copy of myself.

848
01:12:46,712 --> 01:12:50,546
Possibly, making these words
here the command for travel.

849
01:12:56,255 --> 01:12:57,847
I don't like guessing.

850
01:12:58,023 --> 01:13:01,015
I need more information.
I need charts, codices.

851
01:13:02,294 --> 01:13:03,693
Right.

852
01:13:03,796 --> 01:13:05,764
And where might we find those?

853
01:13:07,633 --> 01:13:09,601
In the Hall of Science.

854
01:13:11,404 --> 01:13:13,372
And where's that?

855
01:13:14,140 --> 01:13:15,573
Helium.

856
01:13:15,841 --> 01:13:19,641
Then quick, let's just head on
and turn on back to Helium.

857
01:13:20,079 --> 01:13:21,171
What do you take me for?

858
01:13:21,280 --> 01:13:23,578
I take you for a man who's lost.

859
01:13:23,949 --> 01:13:26,213
I won't be lost if you just tell me
how to work this thing!

860
01:13:26,318 --> 01:13:27,342
I will!

861
01:13:27,453 --> 01:13:30,286
But everything I need to understand
that medallion is in Helium.

862
01:13:30,723 --> 01:13:33,317
I'm trying to get you back
to your cave of gold.

863
01:13:33,459 --> 01:13:34,926
Isn't that what you want?

864
01:13:35,094 --> 01:13:36,288
Yes.

865
01:13:39,698 --> 01:13:40,722
No.

866
01:13:42,334 --> 01:13:44,302
I don't believe you.

867
01:13:45,638 --> 01:13:47,902
We may have been born worlds apart,

868
01:13:50,409 --> 01:13:53,071
but I know you, John Carter.

869
01:13:53,946 --> 01:13:57,609
From the moment
you caught me in the sky, I knew.

870
01:13:59,452 --> 01:14:03,081
I felt the heart of a man
willing to lay down his life for others,

871
01:14:05,357 --> 01:14:08,087
a man willing to fight for a cause.

872
01:14:09,995 --> 01:14:11,758
Here.

873
01:14:13,432 --> 01:14:15,400
On Barsoom.

874
01:14:37,189 --> 01:14:39,384
Don't you see, Carter?

875
01:14:41,861 --> 01:14:43,829
I fled to find another way.

876
01:14:50,002 --> 01:14:52,300
You are the other way.

877
01:14:54,139 --> 01:14:55,128
(LOUD CRASHING)

878
01:14:55,274 --> 01:14:57,242
SOLA: Dotar Sojat!

879
01:15:06,619 --> 01:15:08,246
SOLA: Warhoon!

880
01:15:14,527 --> 01:15:16,051
(YELLS)

881
01:15:17,162 --> 01:15:18,390
(GRUNTS)

882
01:15:18,497 --> 01:15:19,862
Dotar Sojat!

883
01:15:27,473 --> 01:15:29,236
Pursue them to the Aoolian Plain.

884
01:15:29,341 --> 01:15:32,276
Then overtake them
and capture the red woman alive.

885
01:15:32,645 --> 01:15:34,579
The one who jumps?

886
01:15:34,680 --> 01:15:36,614
Let's see what he's capable of.

887
01:15:36,715 --> 01:15:38,580
(MIGHTY ROAR)

888
01:15:43,956 --> 01:15:45,423
(GRUNTING)

889
01:16:00,906 --> 01:16:01,964
(SPURRING)

890
01:16:26,865 --> 01:16:28,059
Sarah!

891
01:16:33,038 --> 01:16:34,972
- Whoa!
- Dotar Sojat!

892
01:16:35,074 --> 01:16:37,542
- What are you doing?
- Sola, get her out of here.

893
01:16:37,676 --> 01:16:39,735
(SCREAMS) Carter!

894
01:16:39,878 --> 01:16:41,778
I was too late once.

895
01:16:41,880 --> 01:16:43,848
I won't be again.

896
01:16:44,016 --> 01:16:45,950
No! No!

897
01:16:46,785 --> 01:16:48,548
(SCREAMS) No!

898
01:16:49,722 --> 01:16:51,155
No!

899
01:16:54,793 --> 01:16:56,090
Woola, go.

900
01:16:57,563 --> 01:16:58,791
Go, damn you!

901
01:17:08,107 --> 01:17:10,075
(YELLS)

902
01:18:01,126 --> 01:18:03,094
(SCREECHING)

903
01:18:22,648 --> 01:18:23,774
Father!

904
01:18:26,919 --> 01:18:28,648
Thank the Goddess!

905
01:18:28,887 --> 01:18:29,979
Carter.

906
01:18:34,827 --> 01:18:36,351
Oh, thank Issus.

907
01:18:36,462 --> 01:18:37,724
TARDOS: Who is he?

908
01:18:37,896 --> 01:18:40,729
His name's John Carter.
He saved my life.

909
01:18:43,569 --> 01:18:45,093
He's from Jasoom.

910
01:18:45,204 --> 01:18:46,296
(SHOCKED MURMURS)

911
01:18:46,405 --> 01:18:47,463
Jasoom!

912
01:18:47,573 --> 01:18:50,633
Zodanga's closer.
He'll have my personal physician.

913
01:18:52,311 --> 01:18:53,938
He shot me out of the sky!

914
01:18:54,046 --> 01:18:55,980
Daughter, listen to me! Listen.

915
01:18:56,915 --> 01:18:59,042
Sab has admitted to everything.

916
01:18:59,518 --> 01:19:02,112
He came to me, alone,
without an escort.

917
01:19:02,888 --> 01:19:04,082
I could have had him imprisoned.

918
01:19:04,189 --> 01:19:05,952
I could have had him killed.

919
01:19:06,058 --> 01:19:08,492
Yet, it was clear he only cared
about your safety.

920
01:19:08,994 --> 01:19:13,226
I feared you'd be tortured by the Tharks
and condemned to die in their arena.

921
01:19:14,700 --> 01:19:16,930
I could not live with that
on my conscience.

922
01:19:17,269 --> 01:19:18,600
I do have one, Princess.

923
01:19:19,505 --> 01:19:20,563
Really?

924
01:19:20,672 --> 01:19:22,606
I thought you had it
removed along with...

925
01:19:24,009 --> 01:19:25,806
She does not trust me, Jeddak.

926
01:19:25,911 --> 01:19:27,572
And why should she?

927
01:19:27,679 --> 01:19:30,409
There's never been trust
between Zodanga and Helium.

928
01:19:31,183 --> 01:19:32,150
Therefore, Princess,

929
01:19:32,251 --> 01:19:34,651
I offer you this small
but sincere token of my goodwill.

930
01:19:42,594 --> 01:19:44,027
My life.

931
01:19:49,568 --> 01:19:51,160
(YELLS)

932
01:19:54,640 --> 01:19:56,608
You hold the power, Princess.

933
01:19:57,476 --> 01:20:01,344
The power of life over me
and over all Barsoom.

934
01:20:02,714 --> 01:20:06,878
With our two cities united,
anything is possible.

935
01:20:09,721 --> 01:20:11,552
All you have to do is marry me.

936
01:20:44,256 --> 01:20:45,587
Is this Helium?

937
01:20:45,691 --> 01:20:47,454
(SCOFFS) No.

938
01:20:48,026 --> 01:20:49,084
(GRUNTS)

939
01:20:49,928 --> 01:20:54,365
Ah, Zodanga, where the men
are as limited as the menu

940
01:20:55,000 --> 01:20:57,901
and the women are as hard as the beds.

941
01:20:58,003 --> 01:20:59,732
What's your business here?

942
01:21:00,105 --> 01:21:01,333
He is my business.

943
01:21:01,440 --> 01:21:04,432
The Jasoomian is to be taken
to more secure accommodation.

944
01:21:04,543 --> 01:21:06,238
We've received no such orders!

945
01:21:06,345 --> 01:21:07,812
You're receiving them now!

946
01:21:08,847 --> 01:21:11,816
Straight from the laughing lips
of Sab Than himself.

947
01:21:14,453 --> 01:21:19,891
I hear that you
are incredibly dangerous.

948
01:21:20,525 --> 01:21:22,015
(LOW VOICE) Take me hostage.

949
01:21:22,728 --> 01:21:25,060
- What?
- Take me hostage.

950
01:21:27,699 --> 01:21:29,132
Are you all right?

951
01:21:29,234 --> 01:21:30,462
(SIGHS)

952
01:21:32,404 --> 01:21:34,702
No! The white imbecile
has taken my sword!

953
01:21:39,244 --> 01:21:40,506
Guards!

954
01:21:42,047 --> 01:21:43,139
Carter! Run!

955
01:21:43,682 --> 01:21:46,480
There's a crazy man
running amok with a sword!

956
01:21:46,752 --> 01:21:48,652
Carter, this way!

957
01:21:54,092 --> 01:21:55,957
Right, your turn.

958
01:21:56,061 --> 01:21:57,790
- My turn?
- Yeah.

959
01:21:57,896 --> 01:22:00,262
- Who are you?
- My name is Kantos Kan.

960
01:22:00,432 --> 01:22:01,922
I serve Princess Dejah.

961
01:22:02,034 --> 01:22:03,296
- Dejah?
- Uh-huh.

962
01:22:03,402 --> 01:22:08,704
And from what she tells me,
you can get us over there.

963
01:22:14,713 --> 01:22:16,044
She said I could make that?

964
01:22:17,416 --> 01:22:18,747
We could always surrender.

965
01:22:18,884 --> 01:22:19,851
Quickly!

966
01:22:19,952 --> 01:22:21,886
Is that what you do on Jasoom?

967
01:22:22,921 --> 01:22:24,548
Come on!

968
01:22:28,961 --> 01:22:30,019
(GRUNTS)

969
01:22:34,666 --> 01:22:35,894
(WOMEN SCREAM)

970
01:22:41,373 --> 01:22:42,431
Hello, ladies.

971
01:22:42,541 --> 01:22:44,065
(GIGGLING)

972
01:22:54,886 --> 01:22:58,014
You are expected
to bow in my presence, Captain Carter.

973
01:23:01,893 --> 01:23:02,882
Bow.

974
01:23:08,400 --> 01:23:10,368
I suppose that will do.

975
01:23:12,604 --> 01:23:14,595
I fetched him, as you commanded.

976
01:23:14,706 --> 01:23:16,037
Thank you, Kantos.

977
01:23:16,141 --> 01:23:18,701
I wish to speak to Captain Carter alone.

978
01:23:19,344 --> 01:23:20,641
Keep watch outside.

979
01:23:23,448 --> 01:23:25,416
Now, girls. Off you go!

980
01:23:36,028 --> 01:23:37,996
(DOOR SHUTS)

981
01:23:39,931 --> 01:23:41,421
You look beautiful.

982
01:23:41,533 --> 01:23:43,524
It's traditional Zodangan,

983
01:23:43,635 --> 01:23:45,535
worn by the groom's mother, I'm told.

984
01:23:46,438 --> 01:23:47,735
A little vulgar for my taste,

985
01:23:47,839 --> 01:23:49,830
but my opinions
are about to become irrelevant.

986
01:23:49,975 --> 01:23:51,966
You can't seriously be considering this.

987
01:23:52,110 --> 01:23:54,408
- What other choice do I have?
- Don't marry him.

988
01:23:54,513 --> 01:23:56,481
Give me a reason not to.

989
01:23:58,183 --> 01:24:00,151
Will you stay and fight for Helium?

990
01:24:03,221 --> 01:24:06,520
Will you stay and fight for Helium?

991
01:24:19,137 --> 01:24:20,126
Dejah.

992
01:24:21,973 --> 01:24:24,066
We have a saying on Barsoom.

993
01:24:25,877 --> 01:24:30,644
A warrior may change his metal,
but not his heart.

994
01:24:35,554 --> 01:24:37,044
You were right.

995
01:24:39,491 --> 01:24:41,356
I could decipher the command.

996
01:24:42,394 --> 01:24:43,759
It's a set of sounds.

997
01:24:45,030 --> 01:24:46,998
A simple phrase.

998
01:24:48,667 --> 01:24:50,567
Repeat after me.

999
01:24:50,702 --> 01:24:53,796
Ock, ohem, ocktei...

1000
01:24:54,172 --> 01:24:56,140
SAB THAN: Open the door!

1001
01:24:59,511 --> 01:25:02,344
Say it now. Ock, ohem, ocktei.

1002
01:25:03,915 --> 01:25:06,577
- (HAMMERING AT DOOR)
- SAB THAN: Are you all right, Dejah?

1003
01:25:06,685 --> 01:25:07,652
Ock,

1004
01:25:07,752 --> 01:25:09,720
ohem,

1005
01:25:12,557 --> 01:25:14,491
ocktei.

1006
01:25:14,593 --> 01:25:15,685
Wies.

1007
01:25:18,964 --> 01:25:20,932
- Wies.
- Jasoom.

1008
01:25:21,299 --> 01:25:22,857
Jasoom. Say it.

1009
01:25:22,968 --> 01:25:24,868
- Say it. Say it!
- Ja...

1010
01:25:26,204 --> 01:25:28,263
Dejah? Are you alone?

1011
01:25:40,585 --> 01:25:42,075
Yes.

1012
01:25:44,289 --> 01:25:46,086
I am alone.

1013
01:25:52,097 --> 01:25:54,065
Well, my Jeddak.

1014
01:25:55,467 --> 01:25:57,435
The moons will soon be rising.

1015
01:25:59,104 --> 01:26:01,470
Let us not delay
the proceedings any further.

1016
01:26:04,776 --> 01:26:06,073
Yes.

1017
01:26:07,312 --> 01:26:09,280
Yes, of course.

1018
01:26:46,518 --> 01:26:47,951
Ssh.

1019
01:26:49,654 --> 01:26:51,622
We'll have plenty of time to talk.

1020
01:26:57,362 --> 01:26:58,454
Now.

1021
01:27:00,999 --> 01:27:02,796
(GROANS)

1022
01:27:02,901 --> 01:27:04,869
Who are you?

1023
01:27:05,670 --> 01:27:07,638
- American.
- Who are you, sir?

1024
01:27:09,374 --> 01:27:12,036
"Sir." Definitely the South.

1025
01:27:13,378 --> 01:27:15,608
The Carolinas? Virginia?

1026
01:27:17,349 --> 01:27:19,283
It's Virginia, isn't it?

1027
01:27:19,384 --> 01:27:21,682
- Lovely place.
- Do you know it?

1028
01:27:21,820 --> 01:27:24,812
Not as well as I should. But I will.

1029
01:27:31,730 --> 01:27:33,129
Padwar, what's the hold-up?

1030
01:27:33,231 --> 01:27:35,028
Sorry, sir. The streets are blocked.

1031
01:27:35,133 --> 01:27:36,361
It's the wedding procession.

1032
01:27:41,072 --> 01:27:43,040
Increased strength and agility.

1033
01:27:44,776 --> 01:27:46,641
Simple matter
of gravitation and anatomy,

1034
01:27:46,745 --> 01:27:48,303
one we ought to have foreseen.

1035
01:27:48,413 --> 01:27:49,812
We?

1036
01:27:50,582 --> 01:27:52,914
No apparent increase in intelligence.

1037
01:27:53,752 --> 01:27:57,119
Still, this will not do at all.

1038
01:27:58,123 --> 01:28:01,058
We can't have Earthmen
projecting themselves over here,

1039
01:28:01,192 --> 01:28:03,854
leaping about, causing
all manner of disruption.

1040
01:28:05,664 --> 01:28:07,188
You're a Thern.

1041
01:28:07,532 --> 01:28:09,500
Therns are a myth.

1042
01:28:10,902 --> 01:28:12,767
Padwar, we'll go on foot.

1043
01:28:12,904 --> 01:28:13,996
Yes, sir.

1044
01:28:23,882 --> 01:28:27,579
My name is Matai Shang,
and I do not exist.

1045
01:28:29,020 --> 01:28:31,454
Indeed, I work very hard at it.

1046
01:28:31,623 --> 01:28:33,591
(CLAMORING)

1047
01:28:34,292 --> 01:28:37,090
Excuse me, excuse me.

1048
01:28:41,633 --> 01:28:46,070
Many pardons... Many pardons.

1049
01:29:01,953 --> 01:29:03,386
It's a shame, really.

1050
01:29:03,488 --> 01:29:06,924
She's a remarkable creature,
and she came very close indeed.

1051
01:29:07,992 --> 01:29:09,357
You mean the Ninth Ray.

1052
01:29:11,629 --> 01:29:13,597
It's of no consequence now.

1053
01:29:14,299 --> 01:29:15,960
After tonight's ceremony,

1054
01:29:16,067 --> 01:29:19,332
when the two moons meet
and vows are exchanged,

1055
01:29:19,804 --> 01:29:22,432
she and anyone else with
knowledge of the Ninth Ray

1056
01:29:22,540 --> 01:29:24,474
will be eliminated.

1057
01:29:25,276 --> 01:29:27,608
In effect, cutting the head off the beast.

1058
01:29:28,346 --> 01:29:31,281
Quick, clean and precise.

1059
01:29:33,385 --> 01:29:34,477
(GASPS)

1060
01:29:35,720 --> 01:29:37,347
Shame there's no one to warn her.

1061
01:29:37,455 --> 01:29:39,423
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

1062
01:29:53,538 --> 01:29:55,506
The balance must be restored.

1063
01:30:01,679 --> 01:30:02,703
(GASPS)

1064
01:30:03,882 --> 01:30:05,747
What gives you the right to interfere?

1065
01:30:05,850 --> 01:30:08,751
What do you care?
This is not your home.

1066
01:30:09,220 --> 01:30:11,780
You have no obligation to these people.

1067
01:30:13,525 --> 01:30:15,823
You don't have a dog in this fight.

1068
01:30:16,261 --> 01:30:18,388
Is that how you would say it in Virginia?

1069
01:30:19,030 --> 01:30:20,497
Man without a cause.

1070
01:30:31,109 --> 01:30:33,077
So what is your cause?

1071
01:30:35,980 --> 01:30:37,948
We have none.

1072
01:30:39,050 --> 01:30:41,712
We're not haunted by mortality
as you are.

1073
01:30:43,621 --> 01:30:46,181
We are eternal.

1074
01:30:46,891 --> 01:30:48,825
I don't understand.

1075
01:30:48,927 --> 01:30:51,088
The wedding, this little stroll.

1076
01:30:52,063 --> 01:30:54,224
Why not just kill me, kill Dejah?

1077
01:30:54,332 --> 01:30:57,392
History will follow
the course we have set, Earthman.

1078
01:30:58,169 --> 01:31:00,637
And we've chosen
Sab Than to rule next.

1079
01:31:02,240 --> 01:31:04,401
The Ninth Ray
must remain in the hands

1080
01:31:04,509 --> 01:31:06,739
of mindless brutes we can control.

1081
01:31:08,780 --> 01:31:12,546
And the infamy of Dejah Thoris's
wedding death will seal his reign.

1082
01:31:14,919 --> 01:31:18,116
We've been playing this game
since before the birth of this planet.

1083
01:31:18,223 --> 01:31:21,454
And we'll continue to do so,
long after the death of yours.

1084
01:31:23,628 --> 01:31:26,893
We don't cause the destruction
of a world, Captain Carter.

1085
01:31:27,732 --> 01:31:29,700
We simply manage it,

1086
01:31:30,468 --> 01:31:32,436
feed off it, if you like.

1087
01:31:34,072 --> 01:31:37,769
But on every host planet, it always
plays out exactly the same way.

1088
01:31:38,843 --> 01:31:42,609
Populations rise, societies divide,

1089
01:31:43,848 --> 01:31:45,816
wars spread.

1090
01:31:47,352 --> 01:31:49,320
And all the while

1091
01:31:50,121 --> 01:31:52,715
the neglected planet slowly fades.

1092
01:32:00,798 --> 01:32:04,029
Prep a two-man flier immediately
for prisoner transport.

1093
01:32:04,135 --> 01:32:05,830
Yes, sir.

1094
01:32:16,180 --> 01:32:17,272
Argh!

1095
01:32:22,287 --> 01:32:24,050
Immortal ain't bulletproof.

1096
01:32:24,188 --> 01:32:25,985
I shot one of you back on Earth.

1097
01:32:32,463 --> 01:32:34,055
Oh, come on.

1098
01:32:39,571 --> 01:32:41,937
I'm trying! I'm trying!

1099
01:32:42,240 --> 01:32:44,299
Guards! After him!

1100
01:32:47,712 --> 01:32:49,009
(SCREAMING)

1101
01:32:55,520 --> 01:32:57,215
(GRUNTS)

1102
01:33:36,961 --> 01:33:38,087
(GRUNTS)

1103
01:33:47,705 --> 01:33:48,933
(GROANS)

1104
01:33:53,411 --> 01:33:55,379
Ohh, Woola!

1105
01:33:56,347 --> 01:33:58,872
I told you Woola would
followyou anywhere.

1106
01:34:00,418 --> 01:34:02,386
He did a lot more than just that.

1107
01:34:05,423 --> 01:34:07,084
Wait! Wait!

1108
01:34:07,225 --> 01:34:08,783
Where are you going?

1109
01:34:08,926 --> 01:34:10,518
To save Dejah.

1110
01:34:10,628 --> 01:34:11,720
And I'll need an army to do it.

1111
01:34:13,164 --> 01:34:14,256
Get on.

1112
01:34:15,366 --> 01:34:18,028
No! Tharks do not fly.

1113
01:34:23,408 --> 01:34:25,376
(APPROACHING WHINE)

1114
01:34:31,716 --> 01:34:32,740
(GRUNTS)

1115
01:34:40,525 --> 01:34:42,186
Gayor.

1116
01:34:51,569 --> 01:34:53,161
Tars! They're going to kill

1117
01:34:55,406 --> 01:34:56,668
Dejah.

1118
01:34:57,041 --> 01:34:59,271
Issus truly rewards the just.

1119
01:35:00,411 --> 01:35:01,605
(GRUNTS)

1120
01:35:02,880 --> 01:35:04,006
(YELLS)

1121
01:35:10,588 --> 01:35:12,055
(CHUCKLES)

1122
01:35:13,925 --> 01:35:15,620
- I see the dead.
- Tars?

1123
01:35:18,696 --> 01:35:20,664
The Virginia I knew

1124
01:35:22,433 --> 01:35:24,401
traveled the Iss.

1125
01:35:26,571 --> 01:35:27,538
What have they done to you?

1126
01:35:28,806 --> 01:35:30,774
Tal challenged.

1127
01:35:31,509 --> 01:35:32,601
I lost.

1128
01:35:34,846 --> 01:35:36,404
Virginia.

1129
01:35:37,548 --> 01:35:40,381
When I saw you leap into the sky,

1130
01:35:41,219 --> 01:35:44,188
I wished to believe it was a sign

1131
01:35:44,489 --> 01:35:47,424
that something new
can come into this world,

1132
01:35:48,292 --> 01:35:53,161
that the greatness of our Thark race
might rise again.

1133
01:35:54,866 --> 01:35:57,232
But it is too late.

1134
01:35:57,335 --> 01:35:59,098
(COUGHS AND SPLUTTERS)

1135
01:35:59,537 --> 01:36:01,505
- Tars.
- No matter.

1136
01:36:02,306 --> 01:36:04,672
My daughter is with
her mother in Paradise.

1137
01:36:04,809 --> 01:36:06,777
There is comfort in that.

1138
01:36:09,514 --> 01:36:12,005
Tars, it's Sola.

1139
01:36:14,719 --> 01:36:16,687
Actually, she's here with me.

1140
01:36:17,054 --> 01:36:18,021
Argh!

1141
01:36:19,624 --> 01:36:20,648
(GROANS)

1142
01:36:22,193 --> 01:36:25,754
This is how you repay your debt to me?

1143
01:36:25,863 --> 01:36:27,125
I need my sword.

1144
01:36:27,231 --> 01:36:30,325
Then it would harvest
your thoughtless head from your body!

1145
01:36:31,402 --> 01:36:33,370
(GRUNTING AND STRAINING)

1146
01:36:34,906 --> 01:36:36,430
(EXHAUSTED SIGH)

1147
01:36:40,511 --> 01:36:42,479
(COUGHS AND SPLUTTERS)

1148
01:36:44,215 --> 01:36:46,183
Up now! We go!

1149
01:36:51,055 --> 01:36:52,716
It is done.

1150
01:36:52,857 --> 01:36:54,290
Nonsense.

1151
01:36:54,392 --> 01:36:57,725
"Leave a Thark his head and one hand,
and he may yet conquer."

1152
01:36:57,862 --> 01:36:59,227
Right?

1153
01:36:59,363 --> 01:37:01,331
Your spirit annoys me.

1154
01:37:04,869 --> 01:37:06,837
(MIGHTY ROAR FROM CROWD)

1155
01:37:18,616 --> 01:37:20,049
JOHN: All this your work?

1156
01:37:20,818 --> 01:37:22,285
Banths.

1157
01:37:29,527 --> 01:37:30,858
Weakness.

1158
01:37:30,962 --> 01:37:32,896
Sentiment.

1159
01:37:33,030 --> 01:37:37,592
Allowing this white worm
to contaminate the horde.

1160
01:37:38,736 --> 01:37:41,864
These are the crimes of Tars Tarkas.

1161
01:37:43,774 --> 01:37:46,937
We are united
because we cull our freaks.

1162
01:37:48,279 --> 01:37:51,612
We are strong
because we despise weakness.

1163
01:37:51,749 --> 01:37:53,683
(MUTTERS OF AGREEMENT)

1164
01:37:57,555 --> 01:38:02,083
Let them be crushed
like unhatched eggs.

1165
01:38:03,094 --> 01:38:04,527
(CHEERING)

1166
01:38:14,305 --> 01:38:16,136
(GRUNTS AND STRAINS)

1167
01:38:17,275 --> 01:38:19,209
(BELLOWING)

1168
01:38:19,443 --> 01:38:21,138
JOHN: Is that a banth?

1169
01:38:21,312 --> 01:38:22,609
No.

1170
01:38:22,747 --> 01:38:24,408
It is a white ape.

1171
01:38:24,515 --> 01:38:26,449
(SCREECHES)

1172
01:38:26,550 --> 01:38:28,541
- (CROWD CHEERS)
- Run!

1173
01:38:29,153 --> 01:38:30,643
(SNIFFING)

1174
01:38:30,755 --> 01:38:33,315
Tars! Get up! Tars!

1175
01:38:33,457 --> 01:38:35,254
Give me your hand!
You have four damn hands!

1176
01:38:35,359 --> 01:38:36,485
Give me one!

1177
01:38:40,698 --> 01:38:42,666
- Father!
- Father?

1178
01:38:47,138 --> 01:38:48,799
JOHN: Tars! Tars!

1179
01:38:49,674 --> 01:38:50,868
Hey!

1180
01:38:50,975 --> 01:38:52,340
(CROWD ROARS)

1181
01:38:52,476 --> 01:38:55,877
Hey! Hey, over here, you blind monkey!

1182
01:39:03,821 --> 01:39:04,947
(GRUNTS)

1183
01:39:13,130 --> 01:39:14,097
(STRAINING)

1184
01:39:14,932 --> 01:39:16,900
Release the other one.

1185
01:39:21,906 --> 01:39:23,874
(CROWD ROARS
ENTHUSIASTICALLY)

1186
01:39:24,008 --> 01:39:25,305
(SIGHS)

1187
01:39:34,418 --> 01:39:38,286
Watch your father die
like the whimpering calot he is!

1188
01:39:38,389 --> 01:39:40,220
(CROWD CHANTING)

1189
01:39:40,358 --> 01:39:42,519
No! Let us watch you!

1190
01:39:45,763 --> 01:39:47,287
(SCREAMS)

1191
01:39:47,431 --> 01:39:48,398
(RIPPING)

1192
01:39:51,535 --> 01:39:53,765
Sola! Are you mad?

1193
01:39:54,005 --> 01:39:56,735
No. The blood of my father drives me.

1194
01:40:02,046 --> 01:40:03,377
(GRUNTS)

1195
01:40:05,116 --> 01:40:06,640
(YELLS)

1196
01:40:13,958 --> 01:40:15,926
(CROWD CHEERS AND WHOOPS)

1197
01:40:19,897 --> 01:40:21,421
(GRUNTING AND STRAINING)

1198
01:40:24,135 --> 01:40:25,261
(YELLS)

1199
01:40:30,107 --> 01:40:31,199
(SNARLS)

1200
01:40:39,316 --> 01:40:41,079
(CROWD ROARS)

1201
01:40:51,295 --> 01:40:52,284
Sola!

1202
01:40:56,634 --> 01:40:58,602
(CROWD GASPS)

1203
01:41:04,675 --> 01:41:06,643
(CHEERING)

1204
01:41:21,625 --> 01:41:24,560
(CHANTING) Virginia! Virginia!
Virginia! Virginia!

1205
01:41:33,137 --> 01:41:35,731
I claim the right of challenge!

1206
01:41:37,875 --> 01:41:38,842
(GRUNTS INQUISITIVELY)

1207
01:41:42,379 --> 01:41:44,313
You have no right to challenge!

1208
01:41:44,448 --> 01:41:46,006
You are not Thark!

1209
01:41:46,884 --> 01:41:48,852
He is Thark!

1210
01:41:48,953 --> 01:41:51,353
He is Dotar Sojat!

1211
01:41:51,889 --> 01:41:56,189
(CHANTS) Dotar Sojat! Dotar Sojat!

1212
01:41:56,660 --> 01:42:00,460
(CROWD CHANTS)
Dotar Sojat! Dotar Sojat!

1213
01:42:00,965 --> 01:42:02,933
(CHANT INCREASES IN PACE)

1214
01:42:04,335 --> 01:42:06,701
Who will pledge their metal to mine?

1215
01:42:10,474 --> 01:42:12,374
(YELLS)

1216
01:42:17,515 --> 01:42:18,846
(WILD CHEERING)

1217
01:42:41,572 --> 01:42:45,702
The Jeddak ofZodanga
means to crush Helium this very night.

1218
01:42:46,210 --> 01:42:48,178
And if Helium falls,

1219
01:42:49,947 --> 01:42:51,915
so does Barsoom.

1220
01:42:52,550 --> 01:42:55,314
We must throw off
the yoke of old hatreds.

1221
01:42:56,387 --> 01:42:58,184
Tharks did not cause this.

1222
01:42:59,557 --> 01:43:02,685
But, by Issus, Tharks will end it!

1223
01:43:02,793 --> 01:43:04,761
(ENTHUSIASTIC CHEERING)

1224
01:43:07,131 --> 01:43:09,190
We ride for Zodanga!

1225
01:43:33,324 --> 01:43:36,521
I know that this is not the fate
you would have chosen for yourself,

1226
01:43:37,094 --> 01:43:38,527
or for Helium,

1227
01:43:38,629 --> 01:43:42,395
but choice is a luxury
even for a Jeddak of Barsoom.

1228
01:43:43,934 --> 01:43:45,663
Even if, in your heart...

1229
01:43:45,769 --> 01:43:47,737
A heart is a luxury.

1230
01:43:51,775 --> 01:43:53,242
MATAl: Steady.

1231
01:43:55,913 --> 01:43:57,881
Remember, she is not the prize.

1232
01:44:00,184 --> 01:44:02,152
The prize is Barsoom.

1233
01:44:04,989 --> 01:44:06,957
(ROAR OF BATTLE CRIES)

1234
01:44:23,841 --> 01:44:25,069
SOLA: You!

1235
01:44:25,175 --> 01:44:26,938
Why is Zodanga undefended?

1236
01:44:27,478 --> 01:44:28,945
Where is everyone?

1237
01:44:29,046 --> 01:44:31,514
The army has been repositioned
outside Helium.

1238
01:44:31,649 --> 01:44:33,412
Only a small contingent remains.

1239
01:44:33,517 --> 01:44:35,576
Sab and Dejah Thoris. Where are they?

1240
01:44:36,320 --> 01:44:38,584
They're at the wedding in Helium!

1241
01:44:38,922 --> 01:44:40,389
Helium?

1242
01:45:00,344 --> 01:45:02,505
TARS: No! I have made my decision.

1243
01:45:02,646 --> 01:45:04,375
It's the only way to get there in time.

1244
01:45:04,815 --> 01:45:07,045
Tharks do not fly.

1245
01:45:08,852 --> 01:45:10,183
So be it.

1246
01:45:15,759 --> 01:45:18,728
This is madness, Dotar Sojat. You'll die!

1247
01:45:21,498 --> 01:45:23,625
Then I'll see you down the River Iss.

1248
01:45:25,035 --> 01:45:26,969
Follow the canal!

1249
01:45:27,071 --> 01:45:29,938
Be careful!
The moonlight will force you to fly low!

1250
01:45:30,040 --> 01:45:31,735
(BARKING)

1251
01:45:33,777 --> 01:45:34,744
(GRUNTS IN FRUSTRATION)

1252
01:45:40,951 --> 01:45:43,579
Like our ancestors before us,

1253
01:45:44,121 --> 01:45:48,854
we gather under the mingled light
of Barsoom's first lovers,

1254
01:45:49,393 --> 01:45:51,759
Cluros and Thuria.

1255
01:46:15,652 --> 01:46:19,315
As the moons
are joined in celestial union,

1256
01:46:19,456 --> 01:46:23,893
so do we unite
Sab Than and Dejah Thoris,

1257
01:46:24,461 --> 01:46:27,191
Zodanga and Helium.

1258
01:46:40,811 --> 01:46:41,869
(COCKS WEAPON)

1259
01:46:41,979 --> 01:46:44,038
No! You'll raise the alarm.
It's one of ours.

1260
01:46:54,158 --> 01:46:55,648
In the time of oceans,

1261
01:46:55,759 --> 01:46:59,092
the celestial lovers
rose from the sea each night

1262
01:46:59,196 --> 01:47:01,130
to consummate their love in the sky.

1263
01:47:01,265 --> 01:47:04,598
Drink now
of this holy water and be wed.

1264
01:47:04,701 --> 01:47:06,669
So may it be again.

1265
01:47:08,138 --> 01:47:10,106
I am yours forever.

1266
01:47:17,214 --> 01:47:19,182
And I am yours

1267
01:47:21,351 --> 01:47:22,409
forever.

1268
01:47:28,325 --> 01:47:29,485
Carter!

1269
01:47:31,528 --> 01:47:33,587
It's a trap! Zodanga's at your walls!

1270
01:47:33,697 --> 01:47:34,994
Now! Do it now!

1271
01:47:35,132 --> 01:47:37,498
- No!
- Helium falls!

1272
01:47:41,305 --> 01:47:42,670
(SCREAMING)

1273
01:47:54,551 --> 01:47:56,348
Zodanga!

1274
01:48:08,098 --> 01:48:09,531
(GRUNTS)

1275
01:48:12,436 --> 01:48:13,903
Dejah!

1276
01:48:14,571 --> 01:48:15,629
Argh!

1277
01:48:15,939 --> 01:48:17,133
(SCREAMING)

1278
01:48:22,379 --> 01:48:23,971
Lfyou'll just get behind me, sir.

1279
01:48:25,249 --> 01:48:26,307
(YELLS)

1280
01:48:30,454 --> 01:48:31,887
Carter!

1281
01:48:33,190 --> 01:48:34,316
(YELLS)

1282
01:48:45,135 --> 01:48:47,433
- It was such a nice wedding.
- Yeah, that.

1283
01:48:58,148 --> 01:49:00,241
Helium's fate is sealed, Earthman.

1284
01:49:00,384 --> 01:49:01,851
As is yours.

1285
01:49:07,257 --> 01:49:09,225
(PANICKED CRIES)

1286
01:49:10,727 --> 01:49:12,695
Thank the Goddess that's over with.

1287
01:49:13,797 --> 01:49:15,765
(BATTLE CRIES)

1288
01:49:19,670 --> 01:49:20,762
(GROANS)

1289
01:49:21,605 --> 01:49:23,095
Virginia!

1290
01:49:28,412 --> 01:49:30,107
It is good to fly!

1291
01:49:34,818 --> 01:49:36,752
By Issus, they fight with us!

1292
01:49:51,234 --> 01:49:52,394
(GRUNTING)

1293
01:49:55,138 --> 01:49:56,105
KANTOS: Brother!

1294
01:49:56,206 --> 01:49:58,174
Heliumite, huh?

1295
01:50:15,459 --> 01:50:17,757
You're going to tell me everything
you know about the Therns.

1296
01:50:17,961 --> 01:50:20,794
You spare me and I'll tell you.

1297
01:50:28,271 --> 01:50:29,238
(CHOKING)

1298
01:50:36,146 --> 01:50:37,511
(CHOKING)

1299
01:50:45,255 --> 01:50:46,222
(GASPS)

1300
01:50:51,261 --> 01:50:55,561
A fitting solution for your setback,
wouldn't you say, Captain?

1301
01:50:57,100 --> 01:50:58,692
Dejah Thoris survives her assassins

1302
01:50:58,835 --> 01:51:00,427
but will fail to prove
her misguided theory

1303
01:51:00,537 --> 01:51:02,505
of the Ninth Ray.

1304
01:51:02,606 --> 01:51:03,903
Yes.

1305
01:51:04,708 --> 01:51:06,676
I'll enjoy playing that out.

1306
01:51:07,077 --> 01:51:08,339
DEJAH: Carter!

1307
01:51:12,015 --> 01:51:13,243
Dejah!

1308
01:51:15,018 --> 01:51:16,417
I'm getting away!

1309
01:51:31,568 --> 01:51:32,592
Tars.

1310
01:51:32,769 --> 01:51:34,259
The medallion.

1311
01:51:34,871 --> 01:51:36,498
Give it to me, my Jeddak.

1312
01:51:44,614 --> 01:51:45,672
No!

1313
01:51:47,751 --> 01:51:48,718
(YELLS)

1314
01:52:05,469 --> 01:52:06,993
I'll explain later.

1315
01:52:14,077 --> 01:52:16,807
TARS: You have won, my Jeddak.

1316
01:52:19,282 --> 01:52:21,045
All is finished.

1317
01:52:25,789 --> 01:52:27,188
Not quite.

1318
01:52:36,166 --> 01:52:37,656
A Jeddak.

1319
01:52:37,801 --> 01:52:39,769
I see you have changed your metal.

1320
01:52:42,105 --> 01:52:43,629
And my heart.

1321
01:52:54,184 --> 01:52:55,617
Dejah Thoris,

1322
01:52:58,822 --> 01:53:01,620
would a princess of Mars
ever consider marriage

1323
01:53:01,725 --> 01:53:05,320
to a wayward Virginia cavalryman

1324
01:53:08,532 --> 01:53:09,863
with nothing to offer?

1325
01:53:10,000 --> 01:53:11,160
Yes,

1326
01:53:13,236 --> 01:53:15,204
John Carter.

1327
01:53:16,373 --> 01:53:17,635
Yes!

1328
01:53:26,383 --> 01:53:29,250
TARDOS: By the ancient rite
of moons and water

1329
01:53:30,720 --> 01:53:32,688
are you bound together,

1330
01:53:34,691 --> 01:53:36,659
husband and wife.

1331
01:53:40,997 --> 01:53:42,965
(CHEERING)

1332
01:54:02,786 --> 01:54:04,754
John?

1333
01:54:27,110 --> 01:54:29,169
Homesick for the Thark nursery?

1334
01:54:30,747 --> 01:54:32,772
I'm sorry. I couldn't sleep.

1335
01:54:34,384 --> 01:54:36,375
I had that feeling you get, suddenly,

1336
01:54:38,154 --> 01:54:41,055
that you left a light burning

1337
01:54:43,460 --> 01:54:45,553
or a door open.

1338
01:54:51,334 --> 01:54:53,359
Go back to bed.

1339
01:54:53,803 --> 01:54:55,896
I won't be long.

1340
01:55:03,980 --> 01:55:05,971
Be back in one xat,

1341
01:55:06,516 --> 01:55:08,575
John Carter of Earth.

1342
01:55:24,501 --> 01:55:26,469
Come.

1343
01:55:56,967 --> 01:55:58,935
John Carter of Earth.

1344
01:56:12,682 --> 01:56:13,876
Yup.

1345
01:56:15,719 --> 01:56:19,780
John Carter of Mars
sounds much better.

1346
01:56:25,261 --> 01:56:28,822
Sire, I must express the deepest
of gratitude for saving Helium.

1347
01:56:28,932 --> 01:56:30,866
Please. The honor is mine.

1348
01:56:31,001 --> 01:56:33,196
Fair enough, Earthman.
Now it's your move.

1349
01:56:33,436 --> 01:56:36,166
Ock ohem ocktei wies Jasoom.

1350
01:56:47,384 --> 01:56:49,352
(CLOTHING CRACKLES)

1351
01:56:50,887 --> 01:56:52,912
(GROANING AND PANTING)

1352
01:56:55,725 --> 01:56:57,750
No, no.

1353
01:57:00,296 --> 01:57:02,093
No.

1354
01:57:02,465 --> 01:57:03,727
Powell?

1355
01:57:13,076 --> 01:57:14,043
No!

1356
01:57:17,047 --> 01:57:19,072
(CRIES OUT)

1357
01:57:26,423 --> 01:57:31,190
Ock ohem ocktei wies Barsoom.

1358
01:57:32,328 --> 01:57:36,924
Ock ohem ocktei wies Barsoom.

1359
01:57:42,806 --> 01:57:45,570
Bars... Barsoom.

1360
01:57:50,914 --> 01:57:55,044
50 million miles apart
and no way to bridge the gap.

1361
01:57:55,151 --> 01:57:58,552
No way to return my body
and my soul to their true home.

1362
01:57:59,522 --> 01:58:02,320
Like a fool,
I had thrown away my medallion.

1363
01:58:05,128 --> 01:58:07,119
Then I recalled Matai Shang.

1364
01:58:07,297 --> 01:58:09,765
His knowledge of Earth, of my history.

1365
01:58:09,966 --> 01:58:12,161
It meant Therns
were a presence on this world.

1366
01:58:12,469 --> 01:58:14,266
The cave in Arizona was proof.

1367
01:58:15,338 --> 01:58:18,068
There might be other such proofs,
other Thern way stations

1368
01:58:18,174 --> 01:58:19,971
hidden all around the world.

1369
01:58:20,110 --> 01:58:23,341
I knew now what the cave
of gold must be used for.

1370
01:58:23,646 --> 01:58:26,410
So for ten bitter years, I searched.

1371
01:58:26,616 --> 01:58:28,277
On the trail of rumor and legend

1372
01:58:28,384 --> 01:58:31,353
I ferreted out every possible
evidence of the Therns,

1373
01:58:31,454 --> 01:58:33,319
but I found no medallion.

1374
01:58:35,525 --> 01:58:38,494
And then it came to me.

1375
01:58:43,366 --> 01:58:46,028
MAN: (SHOUTS AND
WHOOPS EXCITEDLY) I've got it!

1376
01:58:47,070 --> 01:58:48,765
I've found it!

1377
01:58:48,872 --> 01:58:51,272
(EXCITED CHATTER)

1378
01:58:57,113 --> 01:58:59,240
JOHN: And once it came,
there were many plans

1379
01:58:59,382 --> 01:59:01,247
I had to make in secret.

1380
01:59:01,351 --> 01:59:03,410
I could trust no one else.

1381
01:59:03,853 --> 01:59:08,119
I had long suspected that the Therns
were following my movements.

1382
01:59:14,864 --> 01:59:16,832
Sir.

1383
01:59:16,966 --> 01:59:19,127
I feel remarkably unwell, Thompson.

1384
01:59:20,203 --> 01:59:23,331
- Please send for the doctor.
- Yes, sir.

1385
01:59:23,506 --> 01:59:25,474
And, Thompson...

1386
01:59:26,543 --> 01:59:28,443
My attorney as well.

1387
01:59:30,246 --> 01:59:31,804
Of course, sir.

1388
01:59:37,887 --> 01:59:40,856
Now you will understand
the cause of my sudden death.

1389
01:59:46,696 --> 01:59:49,529
The reason
for my bizarre funeral instructions.

1390
01:59:53,102 --> 01:59:56,731
Why the door can only be opened
from the inside.

1391
01:59:58,508 --> 02:00:03,468
For if my body dies on Earth,
then my copy dies on Mars.

1392
02:00:05,748 --> 02:00:06,976
You are the key.

1393
02:00:07,083 --> 02:00:10,314
This is the task I entrust to you
along with all my fortune.

1394
02:00:10,420 --> 02:00:13,651
Protect my body.
The Therns will attempt to destroy it.

1395
02:00:13,756 --> 02:00:15,849
In the time it has taken you
to read these pages,

1396
02:00:15,959 --> 02:00:17,984
they may have already done so.

1397
02:00:18,127 --> 02:00:20,186
(PANTING)

1398
02:00:26,202 --> 02:00:28,193
I am the key. I am the key.

1399
02:00:28,304 --> 02:00:30,397
I, Edgar.

1400
02:00:32,242 --> 02:00:34,233
Ed... Ed...

1401
02:00:34,377 --> 02:00:36,368
E... D...

1402
02:00:36,479 --> 02:00:37,776
Ed!

1403
02:00:37,947 --> 02:00:39,847
It should work!

1404
02:00:50,293 --> 02:00:52,022
Dear Ned.

1405
02:00:54,097 --> 02:00:56,088
You sneaky devil!

1406
02:00:56,232 --> 02:00:59,690
You never called me Edgar!
You... You called me Ned!

1407
02:01:12,148 --> 02:01:13,979
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GASPS)

1408
02:01:21,357 --> 02:01:22,585
Hello, Ned.

1409
02:01:27,363 --> 02:01:30,332
Toxin. Derived from the puffer fish.

1410
02:01:30,500 --> 02:01:32,161
Simulates death.

1411
02:01:38,308 --> 02:01:40,242
You never found the medallion.

1412
02:01:40,343 --> 02:01:41,571
No.

1413
02:01:42,979 --> 02:01:46,039
That's why I'm so grateful
to you for bringing me one.

1414
02:01:47,684 --> 02:01:51,120
I... I was just bait?

1415
02:01:51,354 --> 02:01:54,619
No. You're far more than that.

1416
02:01:55,024 --> 02:01:57,083
I really do need a protector.

1417
02:01:59,162 --> 02:02:01,289
That is, if you're willing.

1418
02:02:10,073 --> 02:02:11,438
Goodbye, Ned.

1419
02:02:16,045 --> 02:02:18,104
Oh, and, Ned...

1420
02:02:19,215 --> 02:02:20,773
Take up a cause.

1421
02:02:20,883 --> 02:02:22,817
Fall in love.

1422
02:02:22,919 --> 02:02:24,477
Write a book.

1423
02:02:26,556 --> 02:02:28,547
It's time I went home.

1424
02:02:39,702 --> 02:02:46,540
Ock ohem ocktei wies...

1425
02:02:48,444 --> 02:02:50,378
Barsoom.

1426
02:02:50,480 --> 02:02:52,072
Barsoom.

1427
